<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1590] AbstractFilter should call vararg method from methods with unrolled parameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1590</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;AbstractFilter should call vararg method from methods with unrolled parameters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would prevent issues like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1511&quot; title=&quot;DynamicThresholdFilter filters incorrectly when params are passed as individual arguments instead of varargs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-1511&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-1511&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in all filter implementations that extend AbstractFilter. Subclasses can override the unrolled vararg methods to provide a garbage-free implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
